messages.text: We just sit around all day. Me and the other new people. They fed us but nobody really talked to us.
No. They R keeping us separate.
I’ll find her. Give it time.
Yeah. They didn’t suspect a thing. U R brilliant.
We just got lucky. Be careful.
Yes. U R on a farm past Route 42. If U have to run, go south from the main entrance. Nearest highway is 2.3 miles.
Did U find a spot for the phone?
Yeah. Shoddy construction. I can stash it in between 2 boards under my cot.
Did they say if U can leave?
Yes. They claim it is voluntary.
U can still back out. I would understand.
Nothing to report. It was just a lot of waiting again. Everyone is antsy. No one really talks to us.
Really bored. They waited all day to feed us. People are complaining and a few asked to leave.
Yeah but they had to put blindfolds on.
I saw a van leave the compound.
Don’t know how much more boredom I can take. It’s weird not having internet or anything to read. If we talk too much, they come in and just stand there.
No. Really calm actually but it shuts everyone up.
More people left today. Only 6 of us now.
Not feeling well. A couple people threw up. I think they may be putting something in the food.
I’ll see how I feel tomorrow. Going to bed.
Everyone is arguing a lot. They searched our bunks. Didn’t find phone.
No. It was standard procedure. Don’t think they are suspicious.
We got out today but did not see Katie.
Basically a hippie commune. Most everyone was gardening. A few buildings like ours. There’s a main house and a barn.
Sunshine helped. But we were only out for a few hours. Feeling drowsy again.
No. I’m OK. Just need sleep.
If I don’t hear from U tomorrow, I call the cops.
They kept us up all last night. They showed us weird films and blared horns. Very trippy.
Yes. Feeling better actually. I slept today and they fed us.
No. They are letting us out more. I’ll find her soon.
He was normal. And nice. Really relaxed.
I know. He talked to each of us in turn. Very sincere.
Don’t worry. I know what this place is.
Why didn’t U say that first?
We spoke briefly. She seemed happy. No duress.
I don’t think so. I may have to take her out by force.
I know. I’ll find out what barracks she’s in.
They R definitely drugging us. I felt hazy all day. Like a trance. Partitions.
This is too dangerous. Pls ask to leave.
No. No guards anymore. We can allowed to go out of the barracks.
I’m not comfortable with this. Ur not making sense.
I’m OK trust me. I’m find her.
Fine. I’ll hold off a little longer.
No. Its good. Less people in house. Barracks R too full.
Can you get out tonight? I’m worried.
Roland invited me into the main house today. I ate dinner with Katie and the chosen.
OK. Thought you were drinking the kool-aid.
Sorry. I’m worried. U need to get out
No shit. I feel like I’m losing my mind in here.
Roland looked through me. Like he was in my head. Talking.
U need to get out tomorrow at the latest. OK?
Calling cops if you don’t reply tonight.
Have a plan. Will get us both out tomorrow night. B ready.
No time. I have to go.
Out of the barracks. U there?
Yes. Parked just outside entrance. Hurry.
Heading to main house. Call cops if I say or don’t reply.
Thank god. Did she come willingly?
No. I had to drug her. I’ll explain when we C U.
Yes. Hurry. I hear something in woods.
U will be fine. Don’t worry.
U will like it here. We are all chosen.
